VwAftLDd,Warlock Pact of the Chain Expanded,JensChup,JSON,Wednesday 20th of September 2023 05:31:49 AM CDT,{""fields"":[{""inline"":false,""name"":""Expanded Familiars"",""value"":""In the Pact of the Chain feature, a warlock can pick an Imp, Pseudodragon, Quasit or Sprite as their familiar, in addition to the existing options in the Find Familiar spell. based on these options, a pact familiar can be any creature with the following characteristics:

- Small or Tiny sized
- Not of the Humanoid creature type
- Maximum of 15 Hit Points
- CR 1 or lower
- Doesn't have a trait that allows them to cast spells.

When considering taking another creature as a familiar outside the given ones, these factors should be considered. Based on the limitations below, here is an example list of other familiars a warlock could take:

- Crawling Claw MM pg44
- Flumph MM pg135
- Gazer VGTM pg126
- Oblex Spawn MTOF pg217
- Quickling VGTM pg187
- Twig Blight MM pg32""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Using Stronger Familiars"",""value"":""In the Eldritch Invocation section in this guide, there are two invocations that allow the warlock to summon more power familiars. The other familiars that can be summoned by these invocations use the same principles as the ones outlined before.

A warlock who has the Restrained Guardian invocation at level 9 can summon any familiar with the following characteristics:

- Medium or smaller sized
- Not of the Humanoid creature type
- Maximum of 35 Hit Points
- CR 2 or lower
- Doesn't have a trait that allows them to cast spells

Similarly, warlocks who take the Shackled Warden invocation  at level 17 can summon any familiar with the following characteristics:

- Large or smaller sized
- Not of the Humanoid creature type
- Maximum of 70 Hit Points
- Cr 3 or lower
- Doesn't have a trait that allows them to cast spells""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Eldritch Invocations"",""value"":""The best way for any warlock to improve the pact boon they have chosen is to select the Eldritch Invocations that require that pact. Below is a list of Eldritch Invocations for Pact of the Chain""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Arcanists Beacon"",""value"":""*Prerequisite: Pact of the Chain feature*
When your familiar uses their reaction to deliver a spell, the spell cast no longer requires a range of touch. If the spell is not the range of self, the range of the spell when cast this way is halved (minimum of 5 feet if longer)""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Branded Mount"",""value"":""*Prerequisite: 5th level, Pact of the Chain feature*
You can cast find steed once using a warlock spell slot. You can't do so again until you finish a Long Rest.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Ghastly Reserve"",""value"":""*Prerequisite: Pact of the Chain feature*
Whenever your familiar uses their reaction to attack or deliver a spell, it gains temporary hit points equal to your Charisma modifier (minimum of 1)""}],""title"":""Pact of the Chain Expanded"",""description"":""These options are all available for those who favour the pact of the chain.

At 3rd level, a warlock can choose the Pact of the Chain from their Pact Boon feature. Part of that feature is adding 4 more Special forms for the familiars that the warlock can choose from. The following is a way to expand those options even further:"",""thumbnail"":{""url"":""https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTJhYITqfMB5yhMbh0-e-alfthMGgYGz5dPVA&usqp=CAU""},""author"":{""name"":""Warlock""},""color"":9442302}"

Z1PStCj4,"Warlock, Invocations Pact of the Seeker - Additional Invocations",JensChup,JSON,Wednesday 20th of September 2023 05:31:07 AM CDT,"{""fields"":[{""inline"":false,""name"":""Path of the Seeker"",""value"":""*Prerequisite: Seeker Patron*
The Seeker bids you to travel in search of knowledge and little can prevent you from walking this path. You can use one of the following options once and need to complete a short or a long rest before doing so again:
- You ignore difficult terrain until the next short/long rest.
- You have advantage on one check to escape a grapple/manacles, or rope bindings.
- You have advantage on one saving throw against being paralyzed.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Seekerâs Speech"",""value"":""*Prerequisite: Seeker Patron*
Your quest for knowledge allows you to master any spoken language. When you complete a long rest, you can pick two languages. You gain the ability to speak, read, and write the chosen languages until you finish your next long rest.""}],""title"":""Pact of the Seeker - Additional Invocations"",""description"":""These invocations are for the homebrew seeker patron."",""author"":{""name"":""Warlock, Invocations""},""color"":9442302}"

CuZwrG2R,Rogue Plague Doctor,JensChup,JSON,Wednesday 20th of September 2023 05:29:36 AM CDT,"{""fields"":[{""inline"":false,""name"":""Medical Training"",""value"":""When you choose this archetype at 3rd level, you gain proficiency with the herbalism kit and the poisoner's kit, as well as the Medicine skill. Your proficiency bonus is doubled for any ability check you make that uses the Medicine skill.

Additionally, any vials from this class or poisons you use add your Intelligence modifier to the save DC to resist them.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""What's in the Vial"",""value"":""Starting at 3rd level, you learn to prepare specialized potions and draughts. At the end of a long rest you may spend time checking your research to see which vials you will prepare for the day. The list of available vials at this level are listed as âlesser vialsâ below. You can prepare 3 lesser vials at level 3 and one additional lesser vial at rogue level 9, 13 and 17.

During the day you can create a number of vials equal to half your rogue level, rounded down, plus your intelligence modifier (minimum of 1). It takes 1 minute to create a vial and you can create any combination of vials from the list you have prepared for that day. Any unused vials expire when you take a long rest and become unusable, becoming a slush of chemicals that taste bad but are not poisonous. Using a vial on yourself or on another creature uses the 'Use an Object' action unless specified otherwise, and you can give the vial to other creatures to be used with their action. Vials are not spells and do not gain any benefit from modif""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Experienced Doctor"",""value"":""Starting at 9th level, when any creature rolls healing for a vial you created or a healing potion you crafted they treat any 1 on a die as a 2.

In addition, you have advantage on saving throws to resist diseases and poisons, and when you deal poison damage with a vial or poison you crafted, you can treat any 1 on a die as a 2.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""A Greater Vial"",""value"":""At 13th level you are becoming better at your crafts. At the start of the day you can prepare two vials from the greater vial list. During the day you can spend one minute to create a greater vial. You can craft one greater vial during the day.

At 17th level you can prepare two additional greater vials at the start of each day and youâre able to craft 3 greater vials between long rests. You can create at most one of each of the greater vials in a day.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""A Master At Your Craft"",""value"":""Starting at 17th level, When you deal poison damage with a vial or poison you crafted, you can roll one of the poisonâs damage dice one additional time and add it to the extra damage of the poison.

In addition to this, whenever you consume or feed someone a vial that restores hp, you can roll one additional die and add it to the total of the roll.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Lesser and greater vials list"",""value"":""The list of lesser and greater vials can be found in [here](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1aXdZgnFJqZ9_WgcgARMbX6MQzleJXleIBZAKPSJOLSE/edit).""}],""title"":""Plague Doctor"",""description"":""You have trained with doctors and medicine men, learning about herbs, tonics, potions, and poisons"",""thumbnail"":{""url"":""https://images-ext-1.discordapp.net/external/862HQTBrBQRc8r4bRMMCebgsFvs5ItBogOhunrI7BRk/https/images-cdn.9gag.com/photo/aEx2YZe_700b.jpg""},""author"":{""name"":""Rogue""},""color"":5198940}"

RgBbQ71d,"Paladin, Matt Mercer, Subclass with adjustments Oath of the Open Sea",JensChup,JSON,Wednesday 20th of September 2023 05:28:50 AM CDT,"{""url"":""https://www.dndbeyond.com/classes/paladin#OathoftheOpenSea"",""fields"":[{""inline"":false,""name"":""Tennets"",""value"":""**No Greater Life than a Life Lived Free.** One should be free to chart their own path without oppression. Those who would exert their power to dominate others shall be smote.

**Trust the Skies.** The guidance of a strong breeze. The rumbling warnings of a coming storm. Nature is a source of portent and council that should be heeded.

**Adapt like the Water.** The waters of the ocean can shift around any obstacle or become an impassable one. They can carve around and reveal the secrets of the past or swallow the truth and hide it forever. To embrace this fluidity is to be ready for any challenge.

**Explore the Uncharted.** The world is filled with much mystery. Through the pursuit of these enigmatic ends, one can both uncover those who hide their dark deeds in shadow to be judged, and find the path to becoming something great.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Oath Spells"",""value"":""You gain oath spells at the paladin levels listed in the Oath of the Open Seas Spells table. See the Sacred Oath class feature for how oath spells work.

```
Paladin level   Spells
====================================
3rd:  Create or Destroy Water, Expeditious Retreat
5th:  Augury, Misty Step
9th:  Call Lightning, Tidal Wave
13th: Control Water, Freedom of Movement
17th: Commune with Nature, Maelstrom```

(The spell list was adjusted since homebrew spells are not allowed on the server)""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Channel Divinity"",""value"":""When you take this oath at 3rd level, you gain the following two Channel Divinity options:

- **Marine Layer.** As an action, you channel the sea to create a thick cloud of fog that surrounds you for 20 feet in all directions. The fog moves with you, remaining centered on you and making its area heavily obscured. You and each creature within 5 feet of you instead treat the area as lightly obscured. This fog lasts for 10 minutes, spreads around corners, and cannot be dispersed unless you choose to end this effect (no action required).

- **Fury of the Tides.** As a bonus action, you can channel the powerful might of the waves to bolster your attacks for 1 minute. Once per turn for the duration, when you hit a creature with weapon attack, you can choose to push the target 10 feet away from you. If the target is pushed into an obstacle or another creature, they take additional bludgeoning damage equal to your Charisma modifier.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Aura of Liberation"",""value"":""Starting at 7th level, you emanate an aura while youâre not incapacitated. You and any creature of your choice within 10 feet of you cannot be grappled or restrained, as well as ignore penalties on movement or attacks while underwater. Creatures that are already grappled or restrained when they enter the aura can spend 5 feet of movement to automatically escape nonmagical restraints.

When you reach 18th level in this class, the range of the aura increases to 30 feet.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Stormy Waters"",""value"":""At 15th level, you can call crashing waters around you as a reaction whenever a creature enters or exits your melee range. The creature takes 1d12 bludgeoning damage and must succeed a Strength saving throw or be knocked prone.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Mythic Swashbuckler"",""value"":""At 20th level, you learn to channel the spirits of historic sea captains to briefly become a paragon of heroic adventure. As an action, you embrace these spirits of the sea to gain the following benefits for 1 minute:

- You have advantage on Strength (Athletics) checks and you gain a climbing speed equal to your walking speed. If you already have a climbing speed, it is doubled.
- If you are within 5 feet of a creature and no other creatures are within 5 feet of you, you have advantage on attack rolls against that creature.
- You can take the Dash or Disengage action as a bonus action.
- You have advantage on Dexterity checks and Dexterity saving throws against effects you can see.

Once you use this feature, you canât use it again until you finish a long rest.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Link"",""value"":""[D&D Beyond](https://www.dndbeyond.com/classes/paladin#OathoftheOpenSea)""}],""title"":""Oath of the Open Sea"",""description"":""The Oath of the Open Sea calls to sea-faring warriors, swashbuckling sailors, and journeying guardians who seek the thrill of an endless horizon. Driven to seek the adventure and mystery across and beneath every endless oceanic expanse, paladins who swear this oath stand against those who would deny the liberties afforded to likeminded travelers, rooting out the tyrannical and corrupt that claim any shore. Such guardians believe in the natural beauty of the sea, often making offerings and prayers to entities or deities like the Wild Mother or Storm Lord that influence safe passage, while often feeling called to hunt those monstrosities that seek to terrorize and spoil the waters with wanton violence and ill intent."",""thumbnail"":{""url"":""https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/778621361907171348/888134412875751424/opensea.jpg""},""author"":{""name"":""Paladin, Matt Mercer, Subclass with adjustments"",""url"":""https://www.dndbeyond.com/classes/paladin#OathoftheOpenSea""},""color"":14917492}"

bs1hgCsa,"Subclass, Paladin Oath of the Hospitalier",JensChup,JSON,Wednesday 20th of September 2023 05:27:58 AM CDT,"{""fields"":[{""inline"":false,""name"":""Tenets of the Hospitaler"",""value"":""**Compassion**. I will be mindful always of my great responsibility to preserve the health and the life of my charges, and I will take any under my care who request it, provided it endangers no one else further.

**Dedication**. I will be ever vigilant in aiding in the general welfare of the community, sustaining its laws and institutions, and not engaging in practices that will in any way bring shame or discredit upon myself or my profession.

**Cooperation**. I will endeavor to work in accord with my colleagues in a spirit of progressive cooperation and never by word or by act cast imputations upon them or their rightful practices.

**Cultivation**. I will attend to my own health, well.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Oath Spells"",""value"":""You gain oath spells at the paladin levels listed in the Oath of the Hospitaler Spells table. See the Sacred Oath class feature for how oath spells work.
```
Paladin level   Spells
====================================
3rd:  Healing Word, Protection from Evil and Good
5th:  Warding Bond, Prayer of Healing 
9th:  Protection from Energy, Revivify  
13th: Death Ward, Dimension Door 
17th: Greater Restoration, Mass Cure Wounds```""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Channel Divinity"",""value"":""When you take this oath at 3rd level, you gain the following two Channel Divinity options:""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""- Rescuer's Lifeline"",""value"":""You can conjure a cord of light to evacuate or intervene, using your Channel Divinity. When an ally you can see within 30 feet of you is hit by an attack, you can use your reaction to choose to either move that character to an empty space adjacent to you or for you to move to an empty space adjacent to the chosen ally. In either case, the chosen ally gains resistance to all damage from the triggering attack. This movement does not provoke attacks of opportunity, and pulls the target along the most direct path, moving them over obstacles if necessary.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""- Swords into Plowshares"",""value"":""When you use your Divine Smite, you can channel it into a replenishing helix, using your Channel Divinity. When you use your Divine Smite roll a number of d8's dependent on the level of the spell slot spent for the smite. The amount of dice is 2d8 for a 1st-level spell slot, plus 1d8 for each spell level higher than 1st, to a maximum of 5d8. The amount increases by 1d8 if the target of the smite was an undead or a fiend and again by 1d8 if you applied the Improved Divine Smite feature, to a maximum of 7d8. You regain points of your Lay on Hands equal the total amount rolled this way.

The amount of points regained this way can be more than your current maximum capacity of lay on hands. Extra points not spent within 1 minute are lost. You cannot use this ability more than once on the same Divine Smite and cannot use this ability again if you have points over your maximum capacity for Lay on Hands.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Aura of Benevolence"",""value"":""Starting at 7th level,  while you are conscious, paladin features and spells that do not deal damage and require you to touch a target can be used as if the target creature is adjacent to you if they are within 10 ft. of you.

At 18th level, this range increases to 30 feet.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Sound Mind, Sound Body"",""value"":""Beginning at 15th level, when you remove a poison, disease, or harmful condition from an ally that was caused by a hostile creature or effect using your Lay on Hands, Cleansing Touch, or a Paladin spell, that ally gains temporary hit points equal to your paladin level.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Miracle Worker"",""value"":""At 20th level, you can become a symbol of hope on shining wings. Using your action, you undergo a transformation. For 1 minute, you gain the following benefits:
- Wings sprout from your back and grant you a flying speed of 60 feet.
- You gain an additional action on each of your turns. That action can be used only to use Lay on Hands, Cleansing Touch, or to cast a paladin spell of 3rd level or lower with a casting time of 1 action.
- The first time each turn you or a non-hostile creature within 30 feet of you deals radiant damage and/or restores hit points, that creature adds your Charisma modifier (with a minimum bonus of +1) as a bonus to the total amount.

Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a long rest.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""D&D Beyond Link"",""value"":""[Paladin Subclass,  Oath of the Hospitalier](https://www.dndbeyond.com/subclasses/939810-oath-of-the-hospitalier)""}],""title"":""Oath of the Hospitalier"",""description"":""The Oath of the Hospitalier is the path of the compassionate weapon. Known by some as Medic Knights-- these stalwart souls traverse the bloodiest battlefields, the darkest jungles, and the foulest pits of hell to give succor to the sick, the wounded, and the lost. Originally an elite branch of the Boros Legion, Hospitalier Paladins became potent and valuable assets in many of Ravnica's more martially-trained guilds, evolving to incorporate the unjudging compassion of the Selesnya Conclave, the consummate professionalism of the Azorious Senate, and the drive for self-improvement of the Orzhov Syndicate. Regardless of their employer, Hospitalier Knights are sworn not just to the oath of the divine warrior
column2: but of the trained physician. They offer their care to any-- even the foes they defeat, should they surrender and see the folly of standing against a force with one of these mighty war physicians in their midst."",""thumbnail"":{""url"":""https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/702255191902388224/871337900523024424/a8ff5ddd852b8c4d8ee75a3760ee3f14.png""},""author"":{""name"":""Subclass, Paladin""},""color"":14917492}"

column1: cA3UMnLE,"Monk, monastic tradition Way of the Zen Archer",JensChup,JSON,Wednesday 20th of September 2023 05:27:02 AM CDT,"{""fields"":[{""inline"":false,""name"":""Zen Archery"",""value"":""Starting when you choose this tradition at 3rd level, you gain proficiency in Perception and become proficient with Longbows. Additionally, Shortbows and Longbows count as monk weapons for you. Your Short Range for Shortbows increases to 120 ft and for Longbows to 225 ft.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Mirror of Truth"",""value"":""Starting at 3rd level, When you catch a missile with the Deflect Missile feature, and spend a Ki point to Return the Missile, you do this reactionary attack using your Shortbow/Longbow (applying modifiers and range as appropriate). You also make the attack with advantage, dealing an additional damage die using your martial arts die.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Dharma Eyes"",""value"":""Starting at 6th level, you may spend 2 Ki points to give yourself keener eyes for 1 minute, gaining advantage on Perception checks based on Sight for the duration. Furthermore, you may apply half of your proficiency score (rounded down) to your attack rolls with Shortbows and Longbows. This is in addition to your normal proficiency bonus.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Flurry of Bows"",""value"":""Starting at 11th level, your Martial Arts and Flurry of Blows can now be applied to ranged attacks made with a bow, rather than just Unarmed Strikes. In these instances, the ranged attack uses the Martial Arts damage die where applicable and consumes ammo as normal. You cannot use Stunning Strike with this.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Serene Mastery"",""value"":""Starting at 17th level, your Bow attacks score a critical hit on an attack roll of 19 or 20.\n\nAdditionally, you may choose to use your action and expend 3 Ki Points to perform a ranged weapon attack against a number of enemies equal to your Wisdom Modifier (min 1) within your short range. You must select a new target for each shot, roll each attack separately, and expend ammo for each shot as usual. These targets must be within 30 ft of one another. You can Flurry of Blows after this attack.""}],""title"":""Way of the Zen Archer"",""description"":""Monks dedicated to this path apply the principles of their monastic studies to archery. To a Zen Archer, the firing of a bow is an art unto itself, requiring one to be at peace with themselves and the world around them."",""thumbnail"":{""url"":""https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/778621361907171348/888129940350980106/zenarcher.jpg""},""author"":{""name"":""Monk, monastic tradition""},""color"":8250059}"

rtdzLzZV,"Monk, monastic tradition Way of the Sumo",JensChup,JSON,Wednesday 20th of September 2023 05:26:19 AM CDT,"{""fields"":[{""inline"":false,""name"":""Armour of Fat"",""value"":""When you choose this subclass at 3rd level, you fully embrace the discipline and techniques attributed to Sumo Wrestling.

- Your hit point maximum increases by 3 and increases by 1 whenever you gain a level in this class.
- In addition, you gain another way to calculate Unarmoured Defence: While you are not wearing armour or a shield, your AC equals 10 + your Strength modifier + your Wisdom Modifier.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Sumo Stance"",""value"":""Provided you are not wearing armor or a shield, you can use a bonus action at the end of your turn to assume a powerful stance to ready yourself for incoming attacks.

While in this stance, you gain the following effects:

- Your speed becomes 0.
- You gain resistance to bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage from nonmagical attacks. When you reach 11th level, you also gain resistance to magical bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage.
- You may use your reaction to prevent being pushed away or knocked prone against your will, against effects such as Thunderwave, Shove attacks, Dragon Wings, and the like.

You can choose to end this stance at the end of your consecutive turns as a free action.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Reliable Muscle"",""value"":""At 6th level, you fully understand how best to use your hulking mass, and gain the following benefits:

- If you are unsuccessful in a grapple check, you may spend 1 ki point to add your Constitution Modifier to the roll, potentially causing the check to succeed.
- In addition, when you grapple a prone target, they are considered restrained. This lasts until the grapple ends, at which point the target resumes being considered prone.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Foodie"",""value"":""At 11th level, you master the craft of creating the wonderful food that sustains your titanic body.

- You gain proficiency, and expertise with Cooking Utensils. 
- Furthermore, during a short rest you are able to craft a hearty meal for your companions. At the end of your short rest, provided you have been cooking for the duration of the short rest with fresh ingredients, you may roll a Cooking Utensils (Wisdom) check. Depending on your roll, a number of creatures equal to your Wisdom Modifier, and yourself, gain Temporary Health as per the table below. 

```
Skill Check | Temp HP
-----------------------------------
 1-10       |    1 + Monk level
11-15       |  1d4 + Monk level
16-20       |  1d6 + Monk level 
21-26       |  1d8 + Monk level 
26-30       | 1d10 + Monk level
  30+       | 1d12 + Monk level```""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Body-slam"",""value"":""At 17th level, you become a force to be reckoned with. Woe comes to those that are foolish enough to face you.

- You count as one size larger (to a maximum size of large) when determining your carrying capacity and the weight you can push, drag, and lift, as well as grappling, allowing you to target Huge creatures.
- When you have an opponent grappled, you may use an action and expend 3 Ki points to perform a powerful body slam. The target is knocked prone and must make a Constitution saving throw against your Ki Save DC. On a failed save the opponent is knocked to 0 hit points. If it succeeds, it takes 10d10 force damage.""}],""title"":""Way of the Sumo"",""description"":""While most monastic traditions rely on speed, elegance, and agility, you are a powerhouse. Your body is honed for endurance and durability, for one of the most noble of sports
column2: wrestling. Most often, your mountain of muscle is covered by an even thicker armor of fat. While most people see you as unfit and helpless, you are the exact opposite."",""thumbnail"":{""url"":""https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ac/Asashoryu_fight_Jan08.JPG/250px-Asashoryu_fight_Jan08.JPG""},""author"":{""name"":""Monk, monastic tradition""},""color"":7005898}"

gx0ynF9u,Monk Way of the Four Elements - Additional Disciplines (Part 2),JensChup,JSON,Wednesday 20th of September 2023 05:25:35 AM CDT,"{""title"":""Avatar of the Elements."",""description"":""As an ultimate display of your mastery of the elements, you can spend 5 ki as an
action to have the elements of earth, fire, air, and water form a protective sphere around your body, gaining multiple benefits for 1 minute. 
While this ability is active, you have resistance to cold, fire, lightning, bludgeoning, and thunder damage.
You can use any of the following abilities as a bonus action for 1 ki point:

- You create a small earthquake on the ground in a 15-foot radius around you. Each creature in that area must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, a creature takes 4d6 bludgeoning damage and is knocked prone.
- You create a line of fire 15 feet long and 5 feet wide extending from you in a direction you choose. Each creature in the line must make a Dexterity saving throw. A creature takes 6d6 fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.
- You create a 15-foot cube of swirling wind centered on a point you can see within 60 feet of you. Each creature in that area must make a Constitution saving throw. A creature takes 2d12 bludgeoning damage on failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. If a Large or smaller creature fails the save, that creature is also pushed up to 10 feet away from the center of the cube.
- You create a 15-foot cone of ice shards extending from your outstretched hand in a direction you choose. Each creature in the cone must make a Constitution save throw. A creature takes 4d8 cold damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. A creature that fails its save against this effect has its speed halved until the start of your next turn."",""thumbnail"":{""url"":""https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRsBotUjJjO4AF6Vy16sA4v_KbUwiHtAf1Lpg&usqp=CAU""},""author"":{""name"":""four elements continued text for level 17 expanded""},""color"":8250059}"

07KPP4eZ,"Monk, Matt Mercer, Subclass with adjustments Way of the Cobalt Soul",JensChup,JSON,Wednesday 20th of September 2023 05:22:51 AM CDT,"{""fields"":[{""inline"":false,""name"":""LVL 3, Extract aspects"",""value"":""Level 3 Extract Aspects learned information changed from all 4 (Condition immunities, Damage Immunities, Damage vulnerabilities and Damage resistances) to 2 of your choice per flurry hit.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""LVL 11, Mind of Mercury"",""value"":""Level 11 Mind of Mercury changed from expending a ki point to get an extra reaction to spending a ki point to attack a creature if it misses you with an attack, without spending your reaction (once per turn).""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Official page"",""value"":""Here is the link to the offical page of the Cobalt Soul monk:

https://www.dndbeyond.com/subclasses/way-of-the-cobalt-soul""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""The subclass"",""value"":""In the fields below, you can see the subclass in full as it is allowed on the server. please give it a read and have fun.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Extract Aspects"",""value"":""Beginning at 3rd level when choosing this tradition, you can strike pressure points to extract crucial information about your foe, granting you insight about their combat ability. Whenever you hit a creature with one of the attacks granted by your Flurry of Blows, you mark them as analyzed. Whenever an analyzed creature misses you with an attack, you can immediately use your reaction to make an unarmed melee attack against that creature. This benefit lasts until you finish a short or long rest.

In addition, you learn choose 2 of the following attributes about the target: Damage Vulnerabilities, Damage Resistances, Damage Immunities, and Condition Immunities.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Extort Truth"",""value"":""At 6th level, you can hit a hidden cluster of nerves on a creature with precision, temporarily causing them to become mentally malleable. If you hit a creature with an unarmed attack, you can spend 1 ki point to force them to make a Charisma saving throw. On a failed save, the creature is unable to speak a deliberate lie and all Charisma checks directed at the creature are made with advantage for up to 10 minutes. You know if they succeeded or failed on their saving throw.

An affected creature is aware of the effect and can thus avoid answering questions to which it would normally respond with a lie. Such a creature can be evasive in its answers as long as the effect lasts.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Mind of Mercury"",""value"":""Starting at 11th level, youâve honed your awareness and reflexes through mental aptitude and pattern recognition. Once per turn, when an creature misses you with an attack, you may spend a Ki point to make an unarmed attack against it, without spending your reaction.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Debilitating Barrage"",""value"":""Upon reaching 17th level, youâve gained the knowledge to temporarily lower a creatureâs fortitude by striking a series of pressure points. Whenever you hit a creature with one of the attacks granted by your Flurry of Blows, you can spend 3 ki points to cause the creature to suffer a vulnerability to a damage type of your choice for 1 minute, or until they take damage of that type. A creature who is affected by this feature cannot be affected by it again for 24 hours.""}],""title"":""Way of the Cobalt Soul"",""description"":""The level 3 and level 11 content of this version have been adjusted as noted below. You are able to use Matt Mercers Cobalt soul monk with these adjustments and not in the form of the Matt Mercer one. This basically overrides it."",""thumbnail"":{""url"":""https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/789832308819623987/817355867723661402/image0.jpg""},""author"":{""name"":""Monk, Matt Mercer, Subclass with adjustments""},""color"":5301186}"

If you're already proficient in it, your proficiency bonus is doubled for any check you make with it.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Battlefield Command"",""value"":""Additionally 3rd level, your prowess in battle allows you to better prepare your allies for the dangers ahead. Select a number of allies equal to your charisma modifier, they will be your chosen allies, whenever you and your chosen allies roll initiative, you gain an additional 1d4 bonus to your initiative checks. You can select different allies at the end of a long or short rest. The bonus increases to 1d6 at 10th level and 1d8 at 18th level.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Tactical Strategist"",""value"":""At 7th level, you learn to use hour battle techniques for better maneuverability. Whenever you reduce a hostile creature to 0 hit points or use the help action on your turn, you can expend your reaction and choose one of the following options:

- You move half your speed without provoking opportunity attacks, and if a hostile creature is within range, you can make one melee weapon attack against them.
- You can cause an ally within 30 feet of you to make a weapon attack against a creature within range.
- You can give yourself and your choosen allies a number of temporary hit points equal to half your fighter level (rounded down) plus your charisma modifier 

This feature can be used a number of times equal to your charisma modifier. You must finish a short or long rest before it can be used again.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Battle Leader"",""value"":""At 10th level, you gain proficiency in charisma saving throws.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Rouse the Troops"",""value"":""Starting at 15th level, when you take a short rest, you aid your allies by giving them advice for battles ahead. Choose one of the following stats, Intelligence, Charisma, or Wisdom, whenever your chosen allies make a saving throw involving the stat you selected, they do so with advantage. You can select a different stat at the end of a short rest.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Warlord Rally"",""value"":""At 18th level, you have mastered the battlefield. You are immune to the Frightened condition. Additionally, if an ally within 30 ft of you ends their turn charmed or frightened, you can use your reaction to remove the condition. If the target is suffering from both conditions, you choose which one is removed.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""DND Beyond"",""value"":""https://www.dndbeyond.com/subclasses/1334764-warlord""}],""title"":""Warlord"",""description"":""Whether it be magic or just pure motivation, these warriors can bolster their allies in any situation. Even going as far as giving them advice and tips, helping friends through times of need, and keeping their spirits high. Warlords are often seen as the leaders and strongest, being expertly trained, they do not falter in the face of danger. Although many envy them, they don't always work with the light-hearted, more often than not, these once noble warriors can get a corrupt view of society, upon being exposed to so many atrocities they deem unfair. Some of them try to take matters into their own hands, often hurting others who didn't deserve it, these twisted-minded folk often battle those whose spirit has not fallen into the darkness in a fight of prowess and morality."",""thumbnail"":{""url"":""https://lanccelot.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Aegis-of-Warlord.jpg""},""author"":{""name"":""Fighter, Martial Archetype""},""color"":9131818}"

LrtmDVS7,"Artificer, Infusions",JensChup,JSON,Wednesday 20th of September 2023 05:20:33 AM CDT,"{""fields"":[{""inline"":false,""name"":""Hover Shield"",""value"":""*Prerequisites: 6th level, A shield*

When you speak its command word, the shield starts hovering over the ground. It has a hover speed of 40 feet and can carry up to 600 lbs, but its speed is halved while carrying over 400 lbs. It can hover up to 5 feet above the ground.

By speaking a command word, it can send the shield to travel alone to a destination within 90 feet of you (it can only move and can not use any actions or reactions). The shield returns to you if you speak the command word again, provided the shield is still within 90 feet of you. This shield has bumping security build in: When meeting a wall, object or creature the shield will stop moving on the square next to it. This shield does not give a bonus to your AC while hovering.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Silent Grappling Hook"",""value"":""*Prerequisites: 6th level, A belt or bracers*

This is a very sturdy cord that is stashed inside your belt or strapped to the side of your bracers. You can spend a bonus action to shoot the cord up to 60 feet in any direction (the length of the cord). It can attach to any one object that is not worn or held. The cord lands silently and can hold up to 500 lbs in strain. You can spend your action and movement to pull yourself to that location. The cord will roll up again. When you are at the place where it landed you can choose whether to loosen the mote without spending an action or bonus action or have it stick there. You cannot shoot a new mote until you have loosened the old one.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Third Arm"",""value"":""*Prerequisites: 10th level, A belt or backpack. (requires attunement)*

A creature wearing this infused item can utilize an additional mechanical arm. This arm has a reach of 5 feet and it can lift a number of lbs equal to 5 times your strength score. You can use the arm to do the following simple tasks: Lift, drop, hold, push or pull an object within its carrying capacity
column2: open or close a door or a container
column4:
no action required.

It canât wield weapons or shields, grapple or shove a creature, use tools or magic items or perform the somatic components of a spell.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Sticky Gloves"",""value"":""*Prerequisite: A pair of gloves or boots*

You can rub these gloves or boots together for one minute to create static electricity, after rubbing them together for one minute you can use these gloves (or boots) to climb up on vertical surfaces and ceilings. As if under the effect of spider climb.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Chest Piece of Salvation"",""value"":""*Prerequisites: 10th level, A shirt, robe or armour that covers the chest*

The first time the wearer drops to zero HP while wearing this garment, it will start to subtly glow while its magic will enter your chest to give you a burst of healing. You regain 1d6 + your characters level in HP and can use your reaction to move up to 10 feet in any direction. This movement does not trigger opportunity attacks. After using this infusion, it will lose its magic and you will need to infuse an item anew in order to be used again.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Earrings of Whispering"",""value"":""*Prerequisite: A set of five earrings*

An Earring of Whispering is a gemmed and enchanted item that delivers and receives Message spells to and from the other connected earrings within five hundred feet. While a creature wears one of the earrings, it can use an action to cast the Message cantrip without Verbal and Material components. The cantrip has a reach of 500 feet. The spell targets all creatures in range that wear one of the other four earrings of this set.""},{""inline"":false,""name"":""Laser pen"",""value"":""*Prerequisite: An ink pen*

You can use an action to aim this pen in a direction of your choosing within 5 feet of you. When you do so, a strong and focused laser appears on the point you choose. This laser can pierce through 1 foot of nonliving material. It takes 1 round (6 seconds) to create a line of 1 foot if you move it. The pan has enough energy to cut a line 20 feet long, after wich it recharges again at the end of a short rest. It would take about a minute to create a hole large enough for a medium creature to fit through, half that time for a small creature, double that time for a large creature, and so on. It has to be held very steadyly, so the target material can not be carried or worn.""}],""title"":""Extra options for Artificer infusions"",""description"":""These infusions are alternative options that can be taken whenever you learn an artificer infusion. These items cannot be turned into magic items and are only usable by artificers."",""thumbnail"":{""url"":""https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/678590361676808192/979709570874212422/o7O8tjNz.png""},""author"":{""name"":""Artificer, Infusions""},""color"":16098851}"

09VDPxqk,A_6,-fury,MySQL,Wednesday 20th of September 2023 04:47:56 AM CDT,"CREATE TABLE e_mp(e_id number PRIMARY KEY,fname varchar(20) NOT NULL,lname varchar(20) NOT NULL,hire_date DATE NOT NULL,job_id varchar2(20) NOT NULL,sale number NOT NULL,dept_id number,CHECK(dept_id>=10))
SELECT fname as emp_name_asc from e_mp ORDER BY fname ASC
SELECT fname as emp_name_dsc from e_mp ORDER BY fname DESC
SELECT hire_date as emp_hire_date_asc from e_mp ORDER BY hire_date ASC
SELECT * from e_mp where fname like 'J%' or fname like 'M%'  ORDER BY lname ASC
SELECT max(sale) as maxxx,min(sale) as minnn,avg(sale) as avggg , sum(sale) as summ from e_mp
SELECT job_id as JOB_D,COUNT(job_id) as E_nos,max(sale) as maxxx,min(sale) as minnn,avg(sale) as avggg , sum(sale) as summ from e_mp GROUP BY job_id
SELECT COUNT(job_id)  from e_mp where job_id like '%MGR%'
SELECT max(sale)-min(sale) as DIFF from e_mp
SELECT max(sale)-avg(sale) as DIFF from e_mp where job_id like '%IT%'
SELECt min(fname) as ROW_Frst , max(fname) as ROW_Last from e_mp
SELECt min(hire_date) as HIRE_Frst , max(hire_date) as HIRE_Last from e_mp
SELECT max(sale) as maxx,avg(sale) as avgg from e_mp where job_id LIKE '%CLERK%'
SELECT dept_id,min(sale) as Lowest_salary from e_mp GROUP BY dept_id
SELECT dept_id,min(sale) as Lowest_salary from e_mp WHERE sale>=3000 GROUP BY dept_id
SELECT fname||' whose Designation is '||job_id||' gets '||sale||' but wants to earn '||3*sale from e_mp
SELECT CURRENT_DATE as TODAY from dual
SELECT e_id,EXTRACT(DAY FROM hire_date) as day,EXTRACT(YEAR FROM hire_date) as Year from e_mp
SELECT fname||' '||lname as Emp_name,TO_CHAR(hire_date,'dd-mon-yyyy') as hired_on from e_mp
SELECT e_id,EXTRACT(MONTH FROM hire_date) as MONTH from e_mp
SELECT fname||' '||lname as Emp_name,e_id,TO_CHAR(hire_date,'dd-mon-yyyy') as hired_on from e_mp
SELECT fname||' '||lname as Emp_name,e_id,TO_CHAR(hire_date,'mon-dd-yyyy') as hired_on from e_mp
SELECT to_char(current_date,'YEAR') as Year_in_words from dual
SELECT TO_DATE(current_date - 15) as Day_minus_15,current_date as curr,TO_DATE(current_date + 15) as Day_plus_15 from dual

8ErKQxNU,[Workshop] Microcontroller,nasdevs,Arduino,Wednesday 20th of September 2023 02:47:54 AM CDT,"const int led_a = 0
const int pins[] = { led_a, led_b, led_c, led_d }
const int number_pins[] = { s_a, s_b, s_c, s_d, s_e, s_f, s_g, s_h }
// The PING))) is triggered by a HIGH pulse of 2 or more microseconds.
// Give a short LOW pulse beforehand to ensure a clean HIGH pulse:
// The same pin is used to read the signal from the PING))): a HIGH pulse
// whose duration is the time (in microseconds) from the sending of the ping
// to the reception of its echo off of an object.
// convert the time into a distance
// According to Parallax's datasheet for the PING))), there are 73.746
// microseconds per inch (i.e. sound travels at 1130 feet per second).
// This gives the distance travelled by the ping, outbound and return,
// so we divide by 2 to get the distance of the obstacle.
// The speed of sound is 340 m/s or 29 microseconds per centimeter.
// The ping travels out and back, so to find the distance of the object we
// take half of the distance travelled.
// e, d, c, dp, g, f, a, b
